answerText: Macau Special Administrative Region [or MSAR][10] With its meaning "fragrant harbor," this territory is famous for the iconic Star Ferry in the Victoria Harbor. It was handed to China in 1999 by Great Britain.

question: Question: It consists of a namesake peninsula as well as the Coloane and Taipa islands.  [10] Identify this former colony on the South China Sea, part of which sits on a peninsula formed by the Pearl River.
